**Segments**

- Based on the type, the packaging adhesives market can be segmented into water-based, solvent-based, hot melt, and reactive.
- By application, the market can be categorized into case & carton sealing, labeling, bags & sacks, folding cartons, corrugated boxes, and others.
- On the basis of packaging type, the market can be divided into flexible packaging, rigid packaging, and others.

The packaging adhesives market is witnessing significant growth due to factors such as increasing demand for packaged food & beverages, growth in the e-commerce industry, and rise in consumer awareness regarding sustainable packaging solutions. Water-based adhesives are gaining traction as they are eco-friendly and comply with regulations regarding volatile organic compounds (VOC) emissions. Solvent-based adhesives are preferred for their fast setting time and high performance, especially in heavy-duty applications. Hot melt adhesives are widely used in the packaging industry for their instant bonding ability and resistance to temperature variations. Reactive adhesives offer excellent bonding strength and durability, making them suitable for challenging packaging materials.

